[[Turkey]] is a founding member of the [[United Nations]],<ref name="Turkey_UN">{{cite web |url=https://www.un.org/Overview/growth.htm |title=Growth in United Nations membership (1945-2005) |author=United Nations |authorlink=United Nations |publisher=United Nations |accessdate=2006-10-30 |date=2006-07-03}}</ref> the Organisation of the Islamic Conference (now the [[Organisation of Islamic Cooperation]]),<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.oic-oci.org/english/main/member-States.htm |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20010221113320/http://www.oic-oci.org/english/main/member-States.htm |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2001-02-21 |title=OIC Membership |author=Organisation of the Islamic Conference |authorlink=Organisation of Islamic Cooperation |publisher=OIC |accessdate=2006-10-30 |year=2006 |df= }} </ref> the [[Organisation for Economic Co-operation and Development]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.oecd.org/document/48/0,2340,en_2649_201185_1876912_1_1_1_1,00.html |title=OECD membership |author=OECD |authorlink=OECD |publisher=OECD |accessdate=2006-10-30 |year=2006}}</ref> and the [[Organization for Security and Co-operation in Europe]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.osce.org/about/13131.html#T |title=OSCE Participating states |author=Organization for Security and Co-operation in Europe |authorlink=Organization for Security and Co-operation in Europe |publisher=OSCE |accessdate=2006-10-30 |year=2005}}</ref> a member state of the [[Council of Europe]] since 1949,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.coe.int/T/E/Com/About_Coe/Member_states/e_tu.asp#TopOfPage |title=Turkey and the Council of Europe |author=Council of Europe |authorlink=Council of Europe |publisher=Council of Europe |accessdate=2006-10-30 |date=2006-10-27 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20061207073323/http://www.coe.int/T/E/Com/About_Coe/Member_states/e_tu.asp#TopOfPage |archivedate = 2006-12-07}}</ref> and of [[NATO]] since 1952.<ref name="TR_NATO">{{cite web |url=http://www.nato.int/multi/photos/1952/m520218a.htm |title=Greece and Turkey accede to the North Atlantic Treaty Organisation |author=NATO |authorlink=NATO |publisher=NATO |accessdate=2006-10-30 |date=}}</ref> Since 2005, Turkey is in [[Accession of Turkey to the European Union|accession negotiations]] with the [[European Union]], having been an associate member since 1963.<ref name="TR_EUChrono">{{cite web|url=http://www.abgs.gov.tr/en/tur-eu_relations_dosyalar/chronology.htm |title=Chronology of Turkey-EU relations |author=Turkish Secretariat of European Union Affairs |authorlink= |publisher=Turkish Secretariat of European Union Affairs |accessdate=2006-10-30 |date= |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070224121529/http://www.abgs.gov.tr/en/tur-eu_relations_dosyalar/chronology.htm |archivedate=2007-02-24 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> Turkey is also a member of the [[G20 industrial nations]] which brings together the 20 largest economies of the world.
Turkey entered [[North Atlantic Treaty Organisation|NATO]] in 1952 and serves as the organization's vital eastern anchor, controlling the straits leading from the [[Black Sea]] to the [[Mediterranean Sea|Mediterranean]] and sharing a border with [[Syria]], [[Iraq]], and [[Iran]]. A NATO headquarters is located in [[İzmir]], and the [[United States]] has maintained air forces at a Turkish base called [[Incirlik Air Base|Incirlik]] that is located near the [[Mediterranean]] city of [[Adana]]. Due to the [[2016–17 Turkish purges]] and Turkey's turn to [[authoritarianism]] some consider expelling Turkey from NATO.<ref>{{cite web|title=Erdogan's purge may give Nato no choice but to expel Turkey from the alliance|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/07/19/erdogans-purge-may-give-nato-no-choice-but-to-expel-turkey-from/|website=|publisher=The Telegraph|accessdate=3 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Wintour|first1=Patrick|title=Turkey officials to demand extradition of Fethullah Gülen from US|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/jul/28/turkey-fethullah-gulen-extradition-coup-attempt|publisher=The Guardian|accessdate=3 March 2017|date=28 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Will Turkey be expelled from NATO?|url=http://www.al-monitor.com/pulse/en/originals/2016/07/turkey-united-states-nato-coup-attempt.html|publisher=Al-Monitor|accessdate=3 March 2017|language=en-us|date=26 July 2016|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170303201317/http://www.al-monitor.com/pulse/en/originals/2016/07/turkey-united-states-nato-coup-attempt.html|archivedate=3 March 2017|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=NATO and Turkey: Allies, not friends|url=http://www.dw.com/en/nato-and-turkey-allies-not-friends/a-19444991|publisher=Deutsche Welle|accessdate=3 March 2017|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Turkey's NATO membership and move to cement ties with Russia|url=https://www.dailysabah.com/columns/merve-sebnem-oruc/2016/08/11/turkeys-nato-membership-and-move-to-cement-ties-with-russia|publisher=DailySabah|accessdate=3 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=In Opinion: Turkey should be thrown out of NATO|url=http://www.newsweek.com/turkey-should-be-thrown-out-nato-489591|publisher=Newsweek|accessdate=3 March 2017|language=en|date=13 August 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=NATO members are supposed to be democratic. What happens when Turkey isn’t?|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/monkey-cage/wp/2016/10/13/nato-members-are-supposed-to-be-democratic-what-happens-when-turkey-isnt/|publisher=Washington Post|accessdate=3 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Weiss|first1=Stanley|title=It's Time to Kick Erdogan's Turkey Out of NATO|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/stanley-weiss/its-time-to-kick-erdogans_b_9300670.html|publisher=The Huffington Post|accessdate=3 March 2017|date=23 February 2016}}</ref>
Turkey is also member of the [[World Trade Organization]] (WTO). It has signed free trade agreements with the [[European Free Trade Association]] (EFTA), Israel, and many other countries. In 1992, Turkey and 10 other regional nations formed the [[Black Sea Economic Cooperation Business Council]] to expand regional trade and economic cooperation.
In December 2000 Turkey became an observer state of the [[Association of Caribbean States]] (ACS).<ref>[http://www.acs-aec.org/PressCenter/NewsReleases/2002/nr062.htm Turkey donates to ACS] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070813010650/http://www.acs-aec.org/PressCenter/NewsReleases/2002/nr062.htm |date=2007-08-13 }}, 21.06.2002</ref>
